      "description": "This E46 M3 is a superlative example of BMW's M-Division engineering, preserved in showroom condition. At its heart is the S54B32 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS system that provides seamless torque delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers short, tactile throws, feeding power to the rear wheels through a perfectly calibrated variable M-differential lock. The chassis is structurally pristine, with a documented subframe reinforcement and a suspension geometry that remains true to factory specifications. Every bushing, seal, and mechanical component reflects a rigorous maintenance schedule, ensuring the signature telepathic steering and balanced weight distribution are fully intact. This is a turn-key, collector-quality vehicle for the discerning purist.",
